{"TopicId":214167,"ForumId":198,"TopicTitle":"Can someone explain this bug (KSC follows ship into space)","CreatedByName":"Tyr Anasazi","CreatedById":128051,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-02T06:48:42Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Tyr Anasazi","CreatedById":128051,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-02T06:48:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I made a big rocket and when I launch it the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E follows me all the way to space at a 90 degrees angle. Kraken comes a bit later and takes the ship apart. This started to happen after I got a previous version of the ship to reach 500 km/s (I want to reach the Kerbiopause)\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022wyEgeCU.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022106.67\u0022 height=\u0022800\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/wyEgeCU.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-02T06:57:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMoved to bug reports\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tazooka","CreatedById":226666,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-02T12:13:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224249543\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022214167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221677739722\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022128051\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tyr Anasazi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Tyr Anasazi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I made a big rocket and when I launch it the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E follows me all the way to space at a 90 degrees angle. Kraken comes a bit later and takes the ship apart. This started to happen after I got a previous version of the ship to reach 500 km/s (I want to reach the Kerbiopause)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI personally haven\u0027t had this bug, but it is common on this forum, Discord, Twitter and Reddit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSometimes it\u0027s a differnet structure following the ship, like a statue or Mun arch\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Agam3rtag2002","CreatedById":227192,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-02T21:34:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was in orbit of the moon, and I left map view and noticed that the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E decided to follow me, it was attached to my rocket for some reason, i\u0027ve done a couple other moon flights now and haven\u0027t run into the issue again. Sadly I have no idea how to replicate the glitch but I do have a video of the me discovering it but I can\u0027t seem to upload it. One other thing I discovered is that the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E wasn\u0027t just a graphical bug it had collision because I then crashed into it a little later.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Agam3rtag2002","CreatedById":227192,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-02T21:39:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBTW if anyone needs to see the clip here it is\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022150\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/RsFXLk52bbo?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022KSC in space\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheAtomicBoy81","CreatedById":227322,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-05T03:54:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know y\u2019all probably got this one a lot, but I just wanted to say that it was ~ at the orbit of jool (I was going to eeloo). Just hope that helps.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Steve7893","CreatedById":226360,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-05T17:37:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat happens if you F5 (quick save) followed by hold F9 (quick reload) ?\u00A0 \u00A0 Does the graphical image persist after the reload?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KhalidE","CreatedById":227476,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-08T01:51:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just completed an orbital slingshot around the Mun to leave the Kerbin \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E. I exit map view upon warping out of Kerbin \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E and EEK! What\u0027s that?!?!?!\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nIt\u0027s the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E! In space!\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://imgur.com/a/2CVZ9zI\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://imgur.com/a/2CVZ9zI\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00228wBXPS6.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.67\u0022 height=\u0022327\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/8wBXPS6.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can see I\u0027m quite far from Kerbin, in orbit over Kerbol, so the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E should clearly not be rendering.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt seems to have matched my orbital speed. It doesn\u0027t move relative to me. When I burn, I accelerate relative to it. If I crash into it, I collide, my craft explodes, and the flight ends. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James Kerman","CreatedById":160462,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-08T06:01:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOverlapping topics have been merged.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"techtox","CreatedById":227618,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-10T00:59:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi all\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m a new player who was very happy to make it back to Kerbin after orbiting around Duna. However, upon trying to get to low orbit around Kerbin, my rocket kept crashing. After loading a save twice I go into Flight view and notice the whole starting area is glitched and I keep crashing into it. I was able to adjust course and still land my mission, luckily!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVersion: 1.0\u003Cbr\u003E\nWindows 10\u003Cbr\u003E\nIntel i5 8600K \u0026amp; RTX 3070 and 16GB RAM\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nNo mods were used at the time\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022120.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1006236867408171078/1081686514964103319/image.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starhawk","CreatedById":131400,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-10T01:38:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBug reports merged.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"techtox","CreatedById":227618,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-10T01:55:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224255896\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022214167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678412323\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022131400\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Starhawk\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, Starhawk said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBug reports merged.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, I\u0027m new and I couldn\u0027t find it \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Starhawk","CreatedById":131400,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-10T01:57:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224255907\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022214167\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221678413307\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022227618\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022techtox\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, techtox said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, I\u0027m new and I couldn\u0027t find it \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo problem and welcome\u00A0 to the forum!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nHappy landings!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dakota","CreatedById":225122,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-27T21:10:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis bug has been 